Jaipur’s most instagrammable background 🩷 Architectural veil! Built so that royal ladies could sip chai and judge in peace- for eyes that saw everything but were never seen. ICONIC QUEEN BEHAVIOUR 🤭

The Hawa Mahal, built in 1799 by Maharaja Sawai Pratap Singh, is a unique five-story palace in Jaipur, India. Designed in the shape of Lord Krishna’s crown, its façade features 953 small windows or jharokhas. The palace combines Rajput and Mughal architectural styles and is known for its intricate latticework and cool breezes, which inspired its name, “Palace of Winds.
